matrix. I like to know that somebody in the world is using and enjoying my works. :)@{ub}@{line}

@ENDNODE


@NODE Main_screen
@{line}@{jcenter}
@{bg highlight}Main screen@{bg back}@{line}
@{jleft}@{line}

     The usage of McAgenda is very simple. Every page contains 30 records that you can handle reading or inserting the data; when a page is full the program will create a new page (you can store up to 990 records, into 33 pages). Records can be protected by a password (see @{"Menu" LINK Menu}), which will be requested on file loading (warning: password is case sensitive).@{line}

     Let's take a look to the record list now. Each entry is represented by a numbered gadget. Clicking on it with the left mouse button will pop up its content. To edit it, just press that gadget with the right mouse button. For those of you who'd like to stay on the keyboard, well, just use your cursor keys to move the arrow ("»"); Spacebar and Enter keys will substitute the mouse buttons.@{line}

     McAgenda provides you with a Case Insensitive search feature. Wildcards are permitted. The first record matching the given pattern will be shown; by "Search Next" you can see all the other eventual matches. See @{"Settings window" LINK Settings_window} for search options.@{line}

     By clicking on "New Record" or pressing right mouse button on an empty record, you can insert a new entry in your database. A record can be erased by holding SHIFT and pressing left mouse button on it.@{line}

     If you are in trouble, you can press the "Esc" key to break whatever operation in progress.@{line}

@ENDNODE


@NODE Menu
@{line}@{jcenter}
@{bg highlight} Menů @{bg back}@{line}
@{jleft}@{line}

McAgenda's menues are activable only when the mouse pointer is @{u}above@{uu} the record list.@{line}

@{b}New@{ub}@{line}
Completely erase your database.@{line}

@{b}Load...@{ub}@{line}
Loads a datafile and uses it as the current.@{line}

@{b}Save@{ub}@{line}
Saves a datafile under the current name.@{line}

@{b}Save as...@{ub}@{line}
Saves the datafile, allows picking a new path and name.@{line}

@{b}Settings...@{ub}@{line}
Opens the @{"settings window" LINK Settings_Window}.@{line}

@{b}Change password...@{ub}@{line}
Asks for a new password to protect your datafile with.@{line}

@{b}Clear password...@{ub}@{line}
Removes your password protection.@{line}

@{b}About...@{ub}@{line}
Something about McAgenda.@{line}

@{b}Quit@{ub}@{line}
Quits.@{line}

@ENDNODE


@NODE Read_Record_Window
@{line}@{jcenter}
@{bg highlight} Read record window @{bg back}@{line}
@{jleft}@{line}

     Left and Right arrow keys will make you browse through all your records, while reading them. @{u}You can also type a key, and McAgenda will go straight to the first record beginning with that character.@{uu}@{line}

     To edit the current record, just click on 'Edit'.@{line}

     While looking for records, you can go to the next hit by clicking on "Search Next". See also @{" Main screen " LINK Main_Screen}.@{line}

     "Dial" issues a dial command to the modem using the string on Field #3 (normally used as "Telephone").@{line}

@ENDNODE


@NODE Editing_Record_Window
@{line}@{jcenter}
@{bg highlight} Editing record window @{bg back}@{line}
@{jleft}@{line}

     Keyboard commands are obviously switched off here, unless you aren't editing anything. With "Ok" you confirm the current record and close the window. With "Abort" your changes are discarder (and the window, yes, it's closed). With "Clear", every field will ... guess it? cleared. :)@{line}

     "Enter" key and "Spacebar" key are possible shortcut to edit the first field. "Tab" and "Shift Tab" will make you wander through all the other ones. "CTRL X" will delete the gadget's contents and "RCOMMAND Q" will undo that. @{line}

@ENDNODE


@NODE Settings_window
@{line}@{jcenter}
@{bg highlight} Settings window @{bg back}@{line}
@{jleft}@{line}

     Here you can define the following settings:@{line}

 @{b}Backup datafile@{ub}: if active, McAgenda will create a backup of data file (named <basename>.bak) before overwriting yours.@{line}

 @{b}Confirm quit@{ub}: if you'd rather like a requester when quitting, well, here's your setting.@{line}

 @{b}Screen Mode@{ub}: asks for the screen mode to be used (the resolution have to be 640x480).@{line}

 @{b}Sort records@{ub}: if active, records will be sorted alphabetically, otherwise they will keep original position.@{line}

 @{b}Search options@{ub}:@{line}
    @{b}Search on Field #.'@{ub}: McAgenda will look for matches in the marked Field contents.@{line}

 @{b}Fields name@{ub}: fields name for each record.@{line}

 @{b}Modem dial string@{ub}: dial string for your modem; "%s" represents the Field #3 (usually used as Phone field).@{line}

@ENDNODE


@NODE ToolType_&_CLI
@{line}@{jcenter}
@{bg highlight} ToolType & CLI @{bg back}@{line}
@{jleft}@{line}

     McAgenda loads its datafile at startup. The default name is "S:McAgenda.data" but you can tell McAgenda to look for another one just passing its name as the first argument (if you're using AmigaShell - i.e. @{b}1.Ram Disk:> McAgenda <path+filename>@{ub}) or using the fitting tooltype (if you launch it from WB).@{line}

     McAgenda recognizes the following ToolTypes:@{line}

 @{b}DATAFILE=<path+filename>@{ub}: Explained above.@{line}

@ENDNODE


@NODE History
@{line}@{jcenter}
@{bg highlight} History @{bg back}@{line}
@{jleft}@{line}

   Major fix reports only.@{line}


v4.5a@{line}
- ScreenMode requester now displays also resolutions greater than 640x256.@{line}

- Wrong text into "About..." requester!   ;-)@{line}

- Added catalog and doc translations in some other languages.@{line}


v4.5@{line}

- Pull down menus added.@{line}

- No more Secret Area. Now you can crypt the whole datafile with a password.@{line}

- Unlimited number of records (well, not exactly: you can store up to 990 records ;-). The program will build a new page in case the previous page is full.@{line}

- Added a gadget which dials the selected number with your modem.@{line}

- Field names are now modifiable.@{line}

- Field name fields are up to 199 letters now.@{line}

- Now you can turn off the automatic sorting.@{line}

- By keeping SHIFT depressed and clicking on a record, you delete the record.@{line}


v4.4@{line}

- Now McAgenda can manage upto 150 records for each areas. Both areas are
splitted into 5 pages.@{line}

- Addes page number on the screen bottom.@{line}

- Modified datafile format.@{line}

- Minor improvements.@{line}


v4.3a@{line}

- Accidentally removed some hotkeys (Esc in windows and Space/Enter in the
main one) in v4.3; fixed. Thanks to "Clc" for the bug report.@{line}


v4.3@{line}

- Localized.@{line}

- Fixed bug in the Public/Secret area management.@{line}

- Minor bugs removed.@{line}


v4.2@{line}

- Source code totally revised, improved and bug fixed.@{line}

- Match gadget accepts wild-cards. If not specified, it assumes
"#?<string>#?".@{line}

- Finally compiled with SAS-C!@{line}

- Modified configuration window and removed some settings.@{line}


v4.1@{line}

- General revision, some functions improved. Added configuration window. Settings are now saved and read from the data file, so some ToolTypes and CLI arguments were removed.@{line}

- Now "Data modified" requester appear only if data were really modified. :)@{line}

- Added "Notes" field. Now default filename is "S:McAgenda.data".@{line}

- Removed two NASTY bugs (now I've got the necessary software to find'em!).@{line}

- FileRequester now use patterns. Improved search function. McAgenda will show its status on the screen's background.@{line}


v4.0@{line}

- Added some functions for the user, such as the search feature. The sort routine has been optimized. Added secret area. General debugging.@{line}


